Fremantle Prison receives international and domestic tourists, as well as ex-prisoners, former prison officers, and their descendants.<ref name="Kumar 2009 Convict Heritage Tourism" />{{rp|205}} Tourist numbers increased each year from 2001/02 to 2009/10, up from almost 105,000 to nearly 180,000 over that period.<ref name="Kumar 2009 Convict Heritage Tourism" />{{rp|210–211}} {{As of|2014}}, the prison has won, been a finalist in, or received other commendation at tourism or heritage awards each year since 2006.{{refn|Fremantle prison won, was a finalist, or received commendation at awards in 2006,<ref name="Midland Reporter awards">{{cite news |title=Prison, Tafe Win Hall of Fame Honour |url=http://midland.inmycommunity.com.au/news-and-views/local-news/Prison-Tafe-win-Hall-of-Fame-honour/7543419/ |accessdate=29 September 2014 |work=Midland Reporter |date=8 December 2009 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140929105455/http://midland.inmycommunity.com.au/news-and-views/local-news/Prison-Tafe-win-Hall-of-Fame-honour/7543419/ |archivedate=29 September 2014 |deadurl=no}} {{Cite additional archived pages |archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6TXMHSOol |archivedate=23 October 2014}}</ref>
