and 2014<ref>{{cite web|author1=Heritage Council|title=Project Details|url=http://awards.stateheritage.wa.gov.au/WAH2014/entry_details.asp?ID=12564&Category_ID=5835|website=2014 Western Australian Heritage Awards|publisher=Government of Western Australia|accessdate=29 September 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140929111537/http://awards.stateheritage.wa.gov.au/WAH2014/entry_details.asp?ID=12564&Category_ID=5835|archivedate=29 September 2014 |deadurl=no}} {{Cite additional archived pages |archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6TXN5DSG1 |archivedate=23 October 2014}}</ref>|group = lower-alpha}} While the tourist experience is based on authenticity and heritage values, some details are concealed or de-emphasised, such as prison tattooing, riots, and graffiti portraying revenge, sexuality, or brutality.<ref name="Kumar 2009 Convict Heritage Tourism" />{{rp|211}}

Attractions include guided tours, a visitors' centre with searchable convict database, art gallery, café, gift shop,<ref name="Kumar 2009 Convict Heritage Tourism" />{{rp|206–208}} and tourist accommodation.<ref name="Sparvell Backpackers Delight" /><ref name="Barnes A Night Inside" /> Educational activities are regularly held for school children, as are exhibitions and re-enactments of historical events. Functions such as theme parties and dinners are held in the prison, with re-enactments serving as entertainment.<ref name="Kumar 2009 Convict Heritage Tourism" />{{rp|206–208}} Tours of the prison show aspects of prison life and recount successful and attempted escapes. Sections of the tunnels are accessible, and night tours focus on the prison's reputation for being haunted.{{refn|group=lower-alpha|There were no reports of ghosts while Fremantle Prison was operational,<ref name="Ayris 2003 Brief History" />{{rp|62}} but it has since developed a reputation as one of Perth's haunted locations.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Perkins |first1=Matthew |title=Haunted Prison? |url=http://www.abc.net.au/local/photos/2008/09/05/2356990.htm?site=perth |accessdate=30 October 2014 |work=720 ABC Perth |publisher=Australian Broadcasting Corporation |date=5 September 2008 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141030070757/http://www.abc.net.au/local/photos/2008/09/05/2356990.htm?site=perth |archivedate=30 October 2014 |deadurl=no}} {{Cite additional archived pages |archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6ThkuRyhQ |archivedate=30 October 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Ebedes|first1=Shannon|title=Perth's Most Haunted locations|url=http://3degree.ecu.edu.au/articles/1390|accessdate=30 October 2014|work=3rd Degree|issue=|edition=10 |volume=4 – Semester 02, 2007|publisher=Edith Cowan University|date=9 November 2007|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110906085357/http://3degree.ecu.edu.au/articles/1390|archivedate=6 September 2011 |deadurl=no}} {{Cite additional archived pages |archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6ThlCHMT9 |archivedate=30 October 2014}}</ref> }}<ref name="Kumar 2009 Convict Heritage Tourism">{{cite journal |last1=Kumar |first1=Kapil |title=Convict Heritage Tourism: A Case Study of Fremantle Prison, Australia |season=Spring |editor-last=Iakovidou |editor-first=Olga |year=2009 |journal=TOURISMOS: An International Multidisciplinary Journal of Tourism |publisher=University of the Aegean |location=Greece |volume=4 |issue=4 |pages=199–214 |url=http://www.chios.aegean.gr/tourism/vol4no4.pdf |accessdate=11 November 2014 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121202205327/http://www.chios.aegean.gr/tourism/vol4no4.pdf |archivedate=23 October 2014 |deadurl=no |format=PDF <!--
